<td width="360" valign="top">
<h3>East:</h3>
<p><b>Corner (125 Walker):</b> In 1982, this building was given 
to a collection of Chinatown agencies to mitigate the 
impact of a new jail built in the neighborhood. 
From 1994-2002, this was 
the Charles B. Wang Community Health Center, 
offering health and social services and education 
to the Chinatown community. The Center subsequently 
moved to <a href="canal.htm">Canal Street</a>.
<br><br>
</td></tr></table>
