<td align="center">
<h2>C<br>E<br>N<br>T<br>R<br>E<br><br>S<br>T<br>R<br>E<br>E<br>T</h2>
</td></tr></table>
</td>

<td width="360" valign="top" >
<table border="2" cellpadding="10" valign="top" bgcolor="FFCC99"><tr>
<td width="360" valign="top">
<h3>East:</h3>
<h3><a href="http://www.ci.nyc.ny.us/html/dcas/html/resources/man_louislefkowitz.shtml" target="_blank" title="Home">
Louis J. Lefkowitz State Office Building</a></h3>
 <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/whoisstan/264250243/" 
title="Former Collect Pond by stan, on Flickr">
<img src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/79/264250243_1a333d84b0_m.jpg" 
width="240" height="180" 
alt="Former Collect Pond by stan, on Flickr" 
 align="right" vspace="4" hspace="4"  /></a> 
<p><b>80 (block):</b> This nine- story building, 
designed by William Haugaard,  
was built from 1928-30 to house state government 
offices. It was renamed in 1984 in honor 
of New York's 
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/1996/06/21/nyregion/louis-j-lefkowitz-22-year-attorney-general-dies-at-91.html" target="_blank" title="Obit">
longest-serving attorney general</a>, 
in office 1957 to 1978.
<a name="worth"></a>
The City Clerk and Marriage Bureau moved their 
offices here from the Municipal Building in 
2009.
<br><br><br>
</td></tr></table>
</td>

