<H2><CENTER> <A href="worth.htm#centre"> W <===</A>
&nbsp; &nbsp; 
WORTH STREET
&nbsp; &nbsp; 
<A href="worth.htm#centre">  ===> E</A></CENTER></H2>
This intersection would have been the southern shore of 
the Collect Pond before it was filled in.
</TD></TR></TABLE>




<table border="0" valign="top"><tr>
<td width="360" valign="top">

<table border="2" cellpadding="10" valign="top"><tr>
<td width="360" valign="top" bgcolor="66FF66">
<h3>West:</h3>

<h2>Foley Square</h2>
 <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/ritzphotos/2352845214/" 
title="Foley Square, NYC by Phillip Ritz, on Flickr">
<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2147/2352845214_989b37ae59_m.jpg" 
width="240" height="160" 
alt="Foley Square, NYC by Phillip Ritz, on Flickr" 
 align="left" vspace="4" hspace="4"  /></a> 
<p>Named for Tammany Hall leader Big Tom Foley 
in 1926, a year after his death. Foley, in 
addition to being an alderman, sheriff, Tammany 
district leader and a mentor of Alfred Smith, 
was a saloonkeeper, and his last joint was 
located where his square is now.

 <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/wallyg/249865562/" 
title="NYC: US Courthouse and Triumph of Human Spirit by wallyg, on Flickr">
<img src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/79/249865562_08e488dbf7_m.jpg" 
width="160" height="240" 
alt="NYC: US Courthouse and Triumph of Human Spirit by wallyg, on Flickr" 
 align="right" vspace="4" hspace="4"  /></a> 
<p>The park in Foley Square is <b>Thomas Paine 
Park</b>, commemorating the great advocate 
for the American Revolution, who died in New York 
City.
<p>The sculpture in 
the <a href="http://www.nycjpg.com/2003/pages/0904.html" target="_blank">fountain</a> here is called 
<a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_things_to_do/attractions/public_art/monuments/african_american_experience/html/image_11.html" target="_blank">
<i>The Triumph of the Human Spirit</i></a>; the boat-like 
shape represents the slave trade and all 
U.S. immigration; the black granite forms 
that rise above the "boat" are patterned 
on African antelope carvings. 
 <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/zkorb/2127000034/" 
title="Foley Square, New York City by Zach K, on Flickr">
<img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2061/2127000034_f55b1decb7_m.jpg" 
width="240" height="159" 
alt="Foley Square, New York City by Zach K, on Flickr" 
 align="left" vspace="4" hspace="4"  /></a> 
<a name="duane"></a>
<p>There was an obscure TV show called 
<i><a href="http://www.tvtome.com/tvtome/servlet/ShowMainServlet/showid-2293/Foley_Square/" target="_blank">Foley Square</a></i>, 
a legal drama that ran for a few months in 1985-86. 

<p>See a <a href="http://www.urban75.org/vista/newyork4.html" target="_blank">
360-degree panorama</a> of Foley Square!
</td></tr></table>


